about.aboutContent:
• Welcome

    Welcome the Colorado Trail Explorer - mobile map!


    COTREX is a online application connecting Coloradans and visitors to rewarding trail experiences by enabling anyone with a browser to explore over 39,000 miles of recreational trails.


    You are currently viewing the mobile version of COTREX which is design for smartphones and tablets. The COTREX - desktop map is designed for devices with a bit more screen real estate and includes more advanced functionality.


  • Get Started

    The key to using COTREX is understanding the maps legend. The color of a line indicates the primary type of recreation allowed on a recreational trail or road:

    Symbol Primary Use Recreational Uses
    Non-mechanized
    Trails
    		 Hike & Hoof
    (hiking, equestrain)
    Non-motorized
    Trails
    		 Multi-use Trails
    (human powered uses)
    Motorized
    Roads & Trails
    		 Cars, OHV, 4x4
    Urban Bike Route Cycling
    Commuting

    Be aware specific uses vary on a trail by trail basis. Click or touch on trails to open a full description.

  • About

    The Colorado Trail Explorer (COTREX) is a product of the Colorado Trail System (CTS) mapping project.


    Colorado Parks and Wildlife (CPW) is leading the CTS effort which aims to map every trail in the state as part of its mission to provide enjoyable and sustainable outdoor recreational opportunities that educate and inspire current and future generations to serve as active stewards of Colorados natural resources.


    Both the CTS data and COTREX online app represent a first iteration. CPW envisions incrementally improving on these 1.0 versions as resources permit.
